01:16:47,235 --> 01:16:48,653
Watch me pulp your face!

1392
01:16:51,072 --> 01:16:52,824
Well, I guess I'm gonna lose, then.

1393
01:16:53,533 --> 01:16:55,035
Oh!

1394
01:16:55,201 --> 01:16:57,412
Don't be like that.

1395
01:16:57,579 --> 01:17:00,582
Here.
I've got a tip for ya.

1396
01:17:00,749 --> 01:17:02,584
Don't let no one get this close.

1397
01:17:02,667 --> 01:17:03,752
<b><font color="#ca004c">[GRUNTS]</font></b>

1398
01:17:05,545 --> 01:17:07,047
<b><font color="#ca004c">[BOTH GRUNTING]</font></b>

1399
01:17:09,549 --> 01:17:11,509
There he is.

1400
01:17:11,676 --> 01:17:15,263
The world's most
notorious fighter, Dalton.

1401
01:17:15,847 --> 01:17:17,057
Put'er there.

1402
01:17:18,725 --> 01:17:19,809
<b><font color="#ca004c">[GRUNTS]</font></b>

1403
01:17:21,061 --> 01:17:24,022
- <b><font color="#ca004c">[YELLS]</font></b>
- <b><font color="#ca004c">[GRUNTS]</font></b>

1404
01:17:29,861 --> 01:17:31,446
<b><font color="#ca004c">[BOTH GRUNTING]</font></b>

1405
01:17:53,176 --> 01:17:54,386
<b><font color="#ca004c">[CREAKING]</font></b>

1406
01:17:54,469 --> 01:17:55,469
<b><font color="#ca004c">[PEOPLE EXCLAIMING]</font></b>

1407
01:18:00,266 --> 01:18:01,518
I got it, I got it, I got it!

1408
01:18:01,601 --> 01:18:02,769
<b><font color="#ca004c">[CRASHES]</font></b>

1409
01:18:06,981 --> 01:18:09,109
<b><font color="#ca004c">[YELLS, GRUNTS]</font></b>

1410
01:18:11,319 --> 01:18:14,447
<b><font color="#ca004c">[YELLING AND GRUNTING CONTINUE]</font></b>

1411
01:18:20,745 --> 01:18:21,746
<b><font color="#ca004c">[SNARLS]</font></b>

1412
01:18:25,667 --> 01:18:27,001
<b><font color="#ca004c">[YELLS]</font></b>

1413
01:18:34,008 --> 01:18:35,051
<b><font color="#ca004c">[YELLS]</font></b>

1414
01:18:42,434 --> 01:18:43,434
<b><font color="#ca004c">[SNARLS]</font></b>

1415
01:18:44,853 --> 01:18:45,853
<b><font color="#ca004c">[PEOPLE EXCLAIMING]</font></b>

1416
01:19:00,702 --> 01:19:02,495
There's something wrong with you.

1417
01:19:05,582 --> 01:19:07,125
Me, too.

1418
01:19:10,962 --> 01:19:14,132
Dex, this is serious!
Are you a cop or what? We need help!

1419
01:19:14,299 --> 01:19:17,343
I sent two cars already, El.
It's the best I could do.

1420
01:19:24,225 --> 01:19:26,269
Dalton.
Dalton.

1421
01:19:26,436 --> 01:19:27,937
Hey! Are you okay?

1422
01:19:31,274 --> 01:19:32,901
Ellie!
Billy's really hurt.

1423
01:19:33,067 --> 01:19:34,068
Ellie!

1424
01:19:36,321 --> 01:19:37,798
- Come on, it's okay. Sit down.
- Fuck!

1425
01:19:37,822 --> 01:19:39,115
He fucked him up really bad.

1426
01:19:39,282 --> 01:19:41,093
- I'm here. What happened?
- Hit him with the golf club.

1427
01:19:41,117 --> 01:19:42,702
That Irish fuck broke my back.

1428
01:19:43,411 --> 01:19:44,412
Fuck.

1429
01:19:45,413 --> 01:19:47,415
<b><font color="#ca004c">[ROCK MUSIC CONTINUES]</font></b>

1430
01:20:27,080 --> 01:20:29,791
Hey. What, are you leaving?

1431
01:20:31,417 --> 01:20:32,835
You're a funny one, Frankie.

1432
01:20:33,461 --> 01:20:35,255
Okay. I mean, yeah...

1433
01:20:35,338 --> 01:20:37,465
I know I wasn't totally
honest with you, all right?

1434
01:20:37,632 --> 01:20:39,552
Brandt wants to take
the Road House away from me.

1435
01:20:41,302 --> 01:20:43,179
You see that?
All up and down the highway?

1436
01:20:43,346 --> 01:20:44,472
Brandt owns all of that.

1437
01:20:45,515 --> 01:20:47,016
And he wants to level it and...

1438
01:20:47,183 --> 01:20:49,561
build some bullshit resort
for a bunch of rich assholes.

1439
01:20:49,727 --> 01:20:52,567
And he needs the Road House to do it.
But I'm not gonna let that happen.

1440
01:20:52,897 --> 01:20:54,649
I'm the last holdout, man.

1441
01:20:54,816 --> 01:20:56,109
You should keep holdin' out.

1442
01:20:57,485 --> 01:20:59,737
Hey. Brandt's out of money.

1443
01:20:59,904 --> 01:21:01,573
And he's borrowing from shady guys.

1444
01:21:02,323 --> 01:21:03,676
And when he doesn't pay them back...

1445
01:21:03,700 --> 01:21:05,076
they're gonna fucking end him.

1446
01:21:05,243 --> 01:21:06,995
All right, well, fuck that guy.

1447
01:21:07,161 --> 01:21:08,371
So, what?
You're leaving now?

1448
01:21:08,538 --> 01:21:10,707
Frankie, I told you from the jump...

1449
01:21:10,873 --> 01:21:12,542
you should've hired that other guy.

1450
01:21:15,295 --> 01:21:16,546
They scared you off?

1451
01:21:17,630 --> 01:21:18,710
Are you really that afraid?

1452
01:21:18,840 --> 01:21:20,216
Yes, I am afraid.

1453
01:21:21,593 --> 01:21:23,344
More than you could ever understand.

1454
01:21:28,516 --> 01:21:30,059
<b><font color="#ca004c">[LIGHTNING CRASHES]</font></b>

1455
01:21:34,355 --> 01:21:37,317
Things didn't exactly go to plan, Mr. B.

1456
01:21:37,942 --> 01:21:40,153
Knox didn't kill the bouncer.

1457
01:21:41,779 --> 01:21:42,779
Mm-hmm.

1458
01:21:43,489 --> 01:21:45,116
Most of our guys are pretty banged up.

1459
01:21:46,159 --> 01:21:49,329
Also, the wrong cops showed
at the Road House, so...

1460
01:21:50,330 --> 01:21:51,789
Big Dick can't help us there.

1461
01:21:57,211 --> 01:21:58,296
What do you want me to do?

1462
01:22:01,049 --> 01:22:03,468
I want you to get me
another bottle from the galley.

1463
01:22:44,592 --> 01:22:46,135
<b><font color="#cf685c">MAN:</font></b> Hey, it's not safe in there.

1464
01:22:46,302 --> 01:22:49,555
Where's the little girl?
That little girl and her father.

1465
01:22:49,722 --> 01:22:51,224
Ambulance took 'em to the hospital.

1466
01:22:51,391 --> 01:22:52,517
Now get out of there!

1467
01:23:27,385 --> 01:23:29,053
<b><font color="#ca004c">[DANCE MUSIC PLAYING INDISTINCTLY]</font></b>

1468
01:23:29,971 --> 01:23:32,223
<b><font color="#ca004c">[INDISTINCT CHATTER]</font></b>

1469
01:23:40,356 --> 01:23:41,482
<b><font color="#ca004c">[WHISTLE]</font></b>

1470
01:23:44,235 --> 01:23:45,445
I didn't hear a car.

1471
01:23:46,028 --> 01:23:47,029
Yeah, well, I walked.

1472
01:23:47,196 --> 01:23:48,531
From the bookstore.

1473
01:23:49,490 --> 01:23:50,825
So, you got our little message?

1474
01:23:50,992 --> 01:23:52,076
I sure did.

1475
01:23:53,494 --> 01:23:54,829
Was that your idea?

1476
01:23:54,996 --> 01:23:56,789
Yeah, she's a cute girl.

1477
01:23:57,331 --> 01:23:58,458
She's kinda stubborn.

1478
01:23:59,417 --> 01:24:00,710
Bit like you.

1479
01:24:05,006 --> 01:24:06,007
You know...

1480
01:24:07,258 --> 01:24:08,801
the funny thing is...

1481
01:24:09,677 --> 01:24:10,928
I was already leaving.

1482
01:24:11,137 --> 01:24:13,139
We finally scared you off, huh?

1483
01:24:13,306 --> 01:24:14,807
Uh, not exactly.

1484
01:24:16,684 --> 01:24:17,935
Just as long as you're scared.

1485
01:24:21,105 --> 01:24:22,105
<b><font color="#ca004c">[GASPING]</font></b>

1486
01:24:22,607 --> 01:24:24,734
I just broke the hyoid bone
in your throat.

1487
01:24:25,610 --> 01:24:27,695
Probably also collapsed your trachea.

1488
01:24:27,862 --> 01:24:29,989
Either way, you won't be
able to breathe anymore.

1489
01:24:35,953 --> 01:24:39,248
You know, it's strange. Somebody else
asked me if I was afraid today.

1490
01:24:40,625 --> 01:24:41,709
I am afraid.

1491
01:24:42,168 --> 01:24:46,214
I'm afraid of what happens
when somebody pushes me too far.

1492
01:24:46,839 --> 01:24:48,299
Somebody just like you.

1493
01:24:51,511 --> 01:24:53,346
'Cause I know what happens next.

1494
01:25:00,311 --> 01:25:01,938
Oh, fuck.
Okay.

1495
01:25:05,441 --> 01:25:06,859
Hey. Hey, man.

1496
01:25:07,026 --> 01:25:08,486
Wow, he looks heavy.

1497
01:25:08,653 --> 01:25:10,154
Good for you.
Um...

1498
01:25:10,655 --> 01:25:12,615
Hey, man, I was just...
I was just leaving...

1499
01:25:13,157 --> 01:25:14,575
you know, for good.
<b><font color="#ca004c">[STAMMERS]</font></b>

1500
01:25:14,909 --> 01:25:16,410
Turns out these guys...

1501
01:25:16,577 --> 01:25:19,455
not as nice as I thought
they were initially.

1502
01:25:20,164 --> 01:25:21,642
I just like riding motorcycles, man...

1503
01:25:21,666 --> 01:25:24,085
but it's really hard to do
in South Florida without a group.

1504
01:25:25,461 --> 01:25:26,295
Hey, man.

1505
01:25:26,462 --> 01:25:28,339
You're not gonna kill me
or anything, right?

1506
01:25:28,506 --> 01:25:29,507
Where's Brandt?

1507
01:25:31,384 --> 01:25:34,279
Okay, I'm gonna be honest with you, man.
They don't tell me much. You know.

1508
01:25:34,303 --> 01:25:35,823
Kinda the last one
to find out about everything...

1509
01:25:35,847 --> 01:25:37,598
which is kinda weird position to be in.

1510
01:25:37,765 --> 01:25:41,435
But I overheard some of
Brandt's guys talking and...

1511
01:25:41,602 --> 01:25:43,242
I guess there's a meeting at Harvest Key.

1512
01:25:43,354 --> 01:25:45,624
Brandt's getting some of the money
that he needs for something.

1513
01:25:45,648 --> 01:25:46,482
It's at 5:00 a.m.

1514
01:25:46,649 --> 01:25:49,235
Which I think is early for a meeting.
Am I right?

1515
01:25:51,028 --> 01:25:52,029
Okay.

1516
01:25:53,155 --> 01:25:56,826
I'll see you.
Thank you for no more violence.

1517
01:25:57,743 --> 01:25:59,370
Good luck with the guy.

1518
01:26:18,639 --> 01:26:20,308
- <b><font color="#ca004c">[SNARLS]</font></b>
- <b><font color="#ca004c">[CROWD CHEERING]</font></b>

1519
01:26:23,519 --> 01:26:25,521
<b><font color="#ca004c">[GRUNTS]</font></b>

1520
01:26:27,148 --> 01:26:28,148
Let him go.

1521
01:26:28,399 --> 01:26:29,775
- Fuck off!
- Stop!

1522
01:26:35,615 --> 01:26:36,782
That's enough! Stop!

1523
01:27:17,031 --> 01:27:19,116
<b><font color="#ca004c">[HELICOPTER WHIRRING]</font></b>

1524
01:27:30,127 --> 01:27:32,088
All right, all right, we're good.

1525
01:27:32,922 --> 01:27:34,256
You wanna count it?

1526
01:27:48,396 --> 01:27:49,397
- Hey!
- <b><font color="#ca004c">[GRUNTS]</font></b>

1527
01:28:12,878 --> 01:28:14,005
Oh, hey, you're awake.

1528
01:28:17,383 --> 01:28:18,551
My boat.

1529
01:28:18,718 --> 01:28:22,179
Yeah. You're gonna be
short one sheriff's boat.

1530
01:28:22,680 --> 01:28:23,681
Sorry.

1531
01:28:24,140 --> 01:28:26,434
- Jesus! Did you just kill him?
- <b><font color="#ca004c">[GUNSHOTS]</font></b>

1532
01:28:27,268 --> 01:28:28,269
Oh, no.

1533
01:28:28,978 --> 01:28:30,658
He's already dead.
I killed him hours ago.

1534
01:28:30,730 --> 01:28:31,772
Is that my gun?

1535
01:28:31,939 --> 01:28:33,441
Yep, sure is.

1536
01:28:33,607 --> 01:28:35,443
Wait.
You don't have to do this.

1537
01:28:35,901 --> 01:28:37,862
Oh.
<b><font color="#ca004c">[SIGHS]</font></b>

1538
01:28:37,945 --> 01:28:39,113
I wish I didn't.

1539
01:28:41,240 --> 01:28:42,491
But I'm angry.

1540
01:28:43,701 --> 01:28:46,495
It takes a lot to get me angry,
but when I am...

1541
01:28:46,662 --> 01:28:49,290
I just can't let go.
I wish I could...

1542
01:28:49,457 --> 01:28:51,917
but your boss and Brandt
really pissed me off.

1543
01:28:53,919 --> 01:28:55,796
They'll know those bullets
didn't kill him.

1544
01:28:56,756 --> 01:28:57,756
Meh.

1545
01:28:58,257 --> 01:28:59,592
It'll just confuse 'em.

1546
01:29:01,469 --> 01:29:03,596
I'll tell 'em it was you.

1547
01:29:03,971 --> 01:29:05,514
Oh, okay!

1548
01:29:07,683 --> 01:29:08,683
You know what though?

1549
01:29:08,809 --> 01:29:11,479
There's a real possibility
you won't remember any of this anyway.

1550
01:29:11,645 --> 01:29:13,481
Wait, wait, what?

1551
01:29:15,441 --> 01:29:17,234
When you've been fighting
as long as I have,

1552
01:29:17,318 --> 01:29:18,986
you know the power of a concussion.

1553
01:29:19,153 --> 01:29:20,793
- Wait.
- A real whack can really knock...

1554
01:29:20,905 --> 01:29:22,698
the short-term memory out of ya.

1555
01:29:22,865 --> 01:29:24,384
Something about how it takes a memory...

1556
01:29:24,408 --> 01:29:26,386
a couple of minutes to get to
the long-term part of your brain.

1557
01:29:26,410 --> 01:29:28,263
I don't know. Anyway, you and I have only
been talking for about a minute and half.

1558
01:29:28,287 --> 01:29:29,413
I don't understand.

1559
01:29:29,580 --> 01:29:31,123
What's that over there?

1560
01:29:32,500 --> 01:29:34,603
<b><font color="#ca004c">[ON PHONE]</font></b> <i>Hello, this is Coast Guard
Chief Petty Officer Williams.</i>

1561
01:29:34,627 --> 01:29:35,461
<i>How can I help you?</i>

1562
01:29:35,628 --> 01:29:37,564
Yes, hi. I just thought you should know
that there's a dead body...

1563
01:29:37,588 --> 01:29:40,132
and a suspicious sheriff's deputy
stranded on Harvest Key.

1564
01:29:40,341 --> 01:29:41,175
<i>Excuse me?</i>

1565
01:29:41,300 --> 01:29:43,862
Yeah, you'll need to get there quick
'cause I already called the local news.

1566
01:29:43,886 --> 01:29:46,206
<i>Can I get a name and callback number
just in case we get...</i>

1567
01:29:52,561 --> 01:29:53,646
Sheriff.

1568
01:30:02,279 --> 01:30:03,531
I just wanna talk.

1569
01:30:04,490 --> 01:30:06,367
Are you here to arrest me again?

1570
01:30:06,450 --> 01:30:08,369
Dalton, listen.
It's Ellie.

1571
01:30:08,536 --> 01:30:09,954
They have her.

1572
01:30:10,121 --> 01:30:11,122
Brandt's got her.

1573
01:30:11,288 --> 01:30:12,957
Wants his money.
The money you took.

1574
01:30:14,458 --> 01:30:15,668
I didn't take any money.

1575
01:30:15,835 --> 01:30:17,419
My deputy told me.

1576
01:30:17,586 --> 01:30:20,089
You were talking some shit
about short-term memory.

1577
01:30:20,214 --> 01:30:21,215
Oh!

1578
01:30:22,675 --> 01:30:23,676
Shit.

1579
01:30:24,176 --> 01:30:25,176
Yeah, I did take it.

1580
01:30:25,302 --> 01:30:26,929
You need to give it back to him.

1581
01:30:27,763 --> 01:30:30,683
Right, you told him I took it?

1582
01:30:31,058 --> 01:30:33,269
It doesn't matter.
He blames me anyway.

1583
01:30:33,435 --> 01:30:34,645
He thinks I'm lying.

1584
01:30:34,812 --> 01:30:37,106
It was my deputy in charge
of the goddamn money.

1585
01:30:37,273 --> 01:30:40,234
If my daughter means anything to you,
you'll help me get her back.

1586
01:30:42,903 --> 01:30:44,321
Dalton, listen.

1587
01:30:45,072 --> 01:30:48,033
He wants the money by noon,
or he says he'll kill her.

1588
01:30:48,200 --> 01:30:49,285
I believe him.

1589
01:30:50,661 --> 01:30:51,829
Please help me.

1590
01:31:00,963 --> 01:31:01,797
Okay.

1591
01:31:01,922 --> 01:31:03,716
Oh, thank God.
Let's get the money...

1592
01:31:03,883 --> 01:31:04,967
It's not here.

1593
01:31:07,511 --> 01:31:08,804
How long will it take?

1594
01:31:08,971 --> 01:31:10,973
I don't know. I hid it.
It's gonna take a while.

1595
01:31:11,682 --> 01:31:13,392
Where should I meet you?

1596
01:31:13,726 --> 01:31:15,019
I like polishing my boat.

1597
01:31:15,186 --> 01:31:18,230
Nothing makes me happier
than to see it all shiny and...

1598
01:31:18,689 --> 01:31:20,733
Oh, hold on, I'll call you back.
Shit. Hey!

1599
01:31:20,941 --> 01:31:21,984
Fuck you doing, man?

1600
01:31:22,109 --> 01:31:23,753
- That's my boat, buddy. Get off!
- Great, you're here.

1601
01:31:23,777 --> 01:31:26,530
You must be the ex-boyfriend.
I'm just looking for the key.

1602
01:31:27,406 --> 01:31:29,033
Ellie told me to come get the boat.

1603
01:31:29,200 --> 01:31:31,327
Here they are.
Bingo!

1604
01:31:32,369 --> 01:31:33,889
You're that bouncer asshole, aren't you?

1605
01:31:33,913 --> 01:31:36,415
Yes, I am that "bouncer asshole."

1606
01:31:36,582 --> 01:31:38,834
You see this right here, pal?
I'm a cop, you idiot.

1607
01:31:39,001 --> 01:31:40,521
Don't worry.
I'll bring it right back.

1608
01:31:40,628 --> 01:31:42,228
No. Hey, you're not goin' anywhere, man.

1609
01:31:43,422 --> 01:31:44,422
Hey!

1610
01:31:45,466 --> 01:31:47,009
You're in trouble.
Back it up.

1611
01:31:47,551 --> 01:31:50,179
It's fine. I'll be back
in a couple hours, all right?

1612
01:31:50,346 --> 01:31:52,056
Nothing is fine about this.

1613
01:31:54,850 --> 01:31:56,644
Okay. Okay.
You got two hours.

1614
01:31:56,810 --> 01:31:58,979
Bring that back without a scratch
on her, you got it?

1615
01:31:59,146 --> 01:32:00,898
Not one scratch.

1616
01:32:01,023 --> 01:32:03,859
Come on, it's water.
How am I gonna get a scratch on it?

1617
01:32:39,395 --> 01:32:42,398
All right.
Let's see what this is about.

1618
01:32:46,610 --> 01:32:48,445
Where the fuck is everyone?

1619
01:33:19,977 --> 01:33:21,061
Thank you, sir.

1620
01:33:22,604 --> 01:33:23,604
Come here.

1621
01:33:23,731 --> 01:33:25,292
Money's not on the boat,
if that's what you're looking for.

1622
01:33:25,316 --> 01:33:26,316
Oh, yeah?

1623
01:33:26,442 --> 01:33:28,694
Man, you were supposed to
bring the money with you.

1624
01:33:28,861 --> 01:33:30,101
Brandt's gonna be disappointed.

1625
01:33:30,154 --> 01:33:31,947
That's okay.
